cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IR. 

This paper deals with the problem of anonymizing dynamic datasets with internal updates, which involves privacy concerns related to data management and security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also introduces theoretical definitions and analysis of dynamic datasets, which suggests a possible fit with cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper proposes a new counterfeited generalization principle, which could be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
